Hey!! 
I’ve recently joined @portsidereg and am starting my career as a full time realtor! It’s definitely a change from my freestyle, but I’m excited to apply the same principles and discipline to provide as much value as I can to my clients! Portside continuously goes the extra mile to provide for clients and for Maine and I’m looking forward to being apart of their journey as a whole! 

Thank you @portsidereg for having me on board and I’m looking forward to working with everyone!!

Don’t worry I’m still training freestyle😘

20 years old today🎉

Who wants to see me back on stage?

Hey everyone! I am now a certified relocation specialist! As a relocation specialist I can assist you with your real estate needs no matter where you are in the world. If you’re searching for a home or looking to sell your home I can connect you with a trusted agent in whatever area you’re in. I’m excited to be able to offer my expertise in all different parts of the world. My relocation network is local AND global🌎 If you’re looking to buy or sell across town or across the world, I can help! Reach out and I’ll help you find a place to call home🏡 I’d be more than happy to explain this more in detail, so feel free to shoot me a message! Looking forward to helping you!!😁

Can I ask what is the point of categories if we don’t use them? Difficulty, Control, Variety, Originality, General.

I approached the judges to ask why I lost vs Aki based on the categories that you’re supposed to be judging with. I was told “if it was a different song you would have won the battle”. Maybe one of the craziest justifications I’ve heard, but ok. Next time I will give the Dj some money before the battle to play a different song and I am in top 8. 

Drops? I had 1 and Aki had 4 drops. Judge tells me “No no no Aki did not have 4 drops no way”. Watch the battle. Who wins on difficulty “Aki” I would love an explanation for this. Absolutely no disrespect to Aki because everyone freestyles in their own way. No hate towards any way of freestyling. However, in no world ever is clutching the ball between your legs and doing slaps for 3 minutes ever going to be more difficult than anything I do. Go try my tricks before you talk to me. Considering the time I put into this sport just to lose because of ridiculous judging is just insane. I will never apologize for speaking my mind and saying the truth. You all know it too.
